        "dealer": "Private Seller Exchange",
        "dealRating": null,
        "imageUrl": "https://images2.autotrader.com/ps-vehicle-media/d5dc192c-31d7-4f2e-b777-aa14375fa97b",
        "source": "autotrader",
        "url": "https://www.autotrader.com/cars-for-sale/vehicle/779404347",
        "whyGood": "At 74K miles with No Accidents and a clean title, this Boxster is competitively priced at $11,250 and only 11.2 miles away. The mid-engine balance makes it the best-handling car on this list by a wide margin. Critically, at 74K miles the IMS bearing is at the sweet spot \u2014 many owners do the upgrade prophylactically at this stage for ~$2K, which effectively eliminates the main risk.",
        "whatToVerify": "IMS bearing service record is the make-or-break item \u2014 ask for documentation or budget $1,500\u20132,500 for the LN Engineering upgrade. Operate top fully. Check convertible top hydraulic cylinders for weeping. Check for coolant leaks at water pump and rear main seal oil leak. Inspect under carpet for water intrusion at windshield frame.",
        "bottomLine": "The benchmark fun car \u2014 if IMS is addressed or documented, this is a once-in-a-decade deal at the price."
      },
